EditorData.NodeContext: Appreciative.

Text.Value: I opened up to you like I have with no one before. We bonded... but it's been downhill from there. Perhaps we can rekindle things, or perhaps not...
I should hope not. Have you ever heard the people who want to talk about themselves? I'm doing you a favour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Casually deflecting from the question

Text.Value: 'Hot bloodedness'? No harm in that...
Honestly, I think I'm caught for words.
Turn to other matters.
No. I can't.
Family? A friend? A lover?
Whole - at last. Thank you, for being by my side through all of this. I never realised I could have a true family - or a true love.
I suppose some would commend our actions - goblins would've razed that whole place to nothing if it weren't for us.
Better than I thought possible. I have done as Lady Shar wished, and she had rewarded me in turn. All is well... or almost. The Nightsinger wants my heart - all of it.
And that's the vessel you chose?

EditorData.NodeContext: Joking

Text.Value: If you're not comfortable, I won't press you.
You pay a high price to serve the Dark Lady - most admirable.
You've had your memories suppressed? That seems... extreme.
Does it even need to be asked? We're beyond me merely liking you - I think I'm a different person, owing to you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Appreciative (and a little disbelieving/teasing of the player's phrasing). High level of respect for player

Text.Value: Really? Some might think it makes me a liability.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly surprised. Referring to her fear of wolves/the player's lack of judgement

Text.Value: What do you think about what happened to the druid grove?
Are you sure? He's large, granted. But I can squeeze in any number of places.
It's a lot to process - nautiloids, tadpoles, the escape, the wilderness... and now I've seen an entire land under the sway of Lady Shar's power.
It's nothing to laugh at. Save your questions if that's how you're going to react.
Lady Shar has chosen me. Words can't convey how I feel. All I know is that I must prove her faith in me to be well-placed...

EditorData.NodeContext: Still processing her new status as Shar's chosen. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar

Text.Value: Personally, I think Halsin's advice about getting to Moonrise sounds like the most promising option.
I mean... I literally can't. There's certain things I can't remember right now.
Let's just say it's a very personal, very private acquaintance.

EditorData.NodeContext: Politely shutting down the topic

Text.Value: If you must know, Baldur's Gate.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cagey. Not enjoying the personal questions.

Text.Value: After all, what I shared with you about my past, about being saved from the wolf... that is not something I would normally even dream of sharing.
It'll make quite a bedtime tale for the children - if I survive to have any, that is.
And secondly, no harm in trying something at least once. Even if you don't ultimately like it.
As for this gith crèche, well... if your kind can actually save us, I stand to be corrected.
I'm not too hopeful that a gith crèche will actually prove our salvation, but worth keeping in mind.
You're not entirely wrong. This is all a little... new.
I... I won't pretend that I don't know what you mean. Ever since we entered the Shadow Curse, I've felt like something's calling to me. Some purpose that I need to find.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wrestling with her beliefs a little, though she's struggling to articulate it fully. Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: You're not the kind of company I'd keep willingly, but all things considered... you'll do.
Though I suppose the only way is up from there. You'll do for now.
I understand. Feel free to have your fun. Perhaps I'll have mine.
I suppose fear doesn't have to be rational. But maybe, given time, I can put it behind me.

Synopsis: Default dialogue - the conversation you can have with Shadowheart at any time when she's a member of your party. You can ask her about herself, or events that you've experienced together during your adventures. Her responses to you may differ slightly depending on her current attitude towards you.
